gomodel:SYNGO_409  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Whole cell patch recordings of P7-P10 calyxes at 22-24 oC were given a 20 ms depolarization from -80 mV to +10 mV. The initial rate of decay of the capacitance change was significantly slower (~33% of control) in the Actin, beta KO suggesting a slower rate of endocytosis following vesicle fusion (Fig 2. A-C). Similar results were observed when the stimulus was changed to a 20 action potential equivalent stimulus (Fig. 2 D-F), performed at 34-37 oC (Fig. 2 G) and in older mice (P13-P14) (Fig. 2 H).\n\nHippocampal neurons were cultured from the Actb LoxP/LoxP mice transfected with Synaptophysin-pHluorin2X (SypH) with or without a Cre containing plasmid (Fig. 6 A and D). SypH can be used to study vesicle recycling as it is non-fluorescent in relatively low pH environment of vesicles but is fluorescent in the higher pH extracellular environment. Upon stimulation the decay of fluorescence was significantly slower than the control (Fig. 6 E-G). This fluorescence was quenchable by a low pH solution applied externally indicating it was not a deficit in vesicle reacidification, but instead suggesting that the vesicles had not been endocytosed (Fig. 6H). This effect was rescued by transfecting Actb in the KO cultures (Fig 7 A,B) but was not rescued by a version of Actb that could not polymerize (Fig 7 E,F). Taken together this data suggests that Actin, beta is important for endocytosis.\n\n.. Experimental description: Krox20 Cre/+;Actb LoxP/LoxP mice were created, which knocked out Actin, Beta in the Calyx of Held. 200 uM parasaggital brain stem slices were cut for capacitance recordings. Actb LoxP/LoxP were used as controls.\n\nMouse hippocampal cultures were prepared using Actb LoxP/LoxP mice. Mice were transfected with a Cre-mCherry plasmid to create knockout.\n\n8/6/2017\nThe species of the over-expression construct (Fig.7) is not relevant for species selection since serving as control for specificity of loss of native mouse protein." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_409" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

